{
  "texts": [
    "It is seen that the Emotiv EPOC EEG headset (N = 33, 15%) is the widely used device.",
    "Moreover, it is observed that few articles used NeuroSky MindWave (N = 11, 5%), and Biosemi Active-electrodes (N = 7, 3%), the Muse headband (N = 3, 2%), and ESI NeusoScan system (N = 3, 1%).",
    "In addition, as can be seen from the table that other BCI devices (Ultracortex Mark IV EEG headset, g.Nautilus, Electro-Cap, CGX Quick-30 EEG, and Quik-cap for NuAmps etc.)",
    "are also used in 11% (N = 24) of the studies but since their number is less than 3 they are not represented in the Figure separately.",
    "63% (N = 135) of the studies do not report any information about the BCI device used.Since various EEG-based BCI devices are used in the studies, the number of channels used for the studies is also varied, too."
  ]
}